    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_ædyly" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ædyly</orth></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>æduli</orth></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>глупый</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>stupid</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>wydis dywwæ ʽvsymæry; īw ʒy wydī zændǵyn, īnnæ ædyly</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>было два брата; один из них был умный, другой глупый</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>there were two brothers; one of them was smart, the other was
                                stupid</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."
                            /><biblScope>146</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>ædylyjy fændaggag razdær fæxærync</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>дорожная провизия глупого съедается в начале (пути)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>travel provisions of the stupid are eaten at the beginning (of the
                                road)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III
                            234</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>wæd ma mæ xonæntæ æduli!</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>пусть тогда еще назовут меня дурнем!</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>then let them still call me a fool!</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Gurdž._Æduli"
                            /><biblScope>77</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>næ færazun mæ mednimær kænun mæxe ædulijæn ænkʼaj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>не могу представить, чтобы я стала супругой дурака</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>I can not imagine that I would become the wife of a fool</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Gurdž._Æduli"
                            /><biblScope>89</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>deli, däli</w>
                        <gloss><q>глупый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>дурак</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>сумасшедший</q></gloss></mentioned>; проникло и в другие
                    кавказские языки: <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/>
                        <w>delä, dejlä</w>
                        <gloss><q>глупый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>дурак</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lez"><lang/>
                        <w>deli</w>
                        <gloss><q>сумасшедший</q></gloss></mentioned>. Появление в начале %iæ%i,
                    осмысляемого, по-видимому, как α privativum, явилось результатом восприятия
                    этого слова как негативного: „не-разумный“, „без-умный“. Может быть, сыграла
                    также роль контаминация с <mentioned xml:lang="ar"><lang/>
                        <w>abdāl</w>
                        <gloss><q>отшельник</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>безумец</q></gloss></mentioned>, ср. <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/>
                        <w>’adal-</w>
                        <gloss><q>глупый</q></gloss></mentioned>. <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>80</biblScope></bibl> выводил
                    из %i*a-turya%i, ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>turas</w>
                        <gloss><q>мощный</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>быстрый</q></gloss></mentioned>. Однако значения плохо
                    вяжутся.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>deli, däli</w>
                        <gloss><q>stupid</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>fool</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>crazy</q></gloss></mentioned>; found its way into other Caucasian
                    languages: <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/>
                        <w>delä, dejlä</w>
                        <gloss><q>stupid</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>fool</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lez"><lang/>
                        <w>deli</w>
                        <gloss><q>crazy</q></gloss></mentioned>. The appearance of %iæ%i at the
                    beginning, which was treated, apparently, as α privativum, was the result of the
                    fact that this word was percepted as negative: “not-intelligent”,
                    “without-intelligent”. Perhaps, contamination with <mentioned xml:lang="ar"><lang/>
                        <w>abdāl</w>
                        <gloss><q>отшельник</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>безумец</q></gloss></mentioned> played its role, cf. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="av"><lang/>
                        <w>’adal-</w>
                        <gloss><q>stupid</q></gloss></mentioned>. <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>80</biblScope></bibl> traced
                    it back to %i*a-turya%i, cf. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>turas</w>
                        <gloss><q>powerful</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>fast</q></gloss></mentioned>. However, the meanings do not fit
                    well.</etym>
            </entry>
